-- tf.h3: How to create custom component, using default attributes?





-- tf.markdown:

`FTD` lang is flexible and you can define your custom names to the default component.
Below are few examples of custom names:

-- cb.code: `-- quote-12` with custom name as e.g. `blog-quote`:
lang: ftd

\-- quote-12.quote-12 blog-quote:
optional caption title:
body body: 
title: $title
body: $body





-- tf.markdown:

How to use above custom name:

-- cb.code: custom `-- blog-quote` usage:
lang: ftd

\-- blog-quote: Swami Vivekananda

"Take up one idea. Make that one idea your life; dream of it; think of it; 
live on that idea. Let the brain, the body, muscles, nerves, every part of 
your body be full of that idea, and just leave every other idea alone. This 
is the way to success, and this is the way great spiritual giants are produced."












